  "prompt": "What are some less fictioned movie everyone must watch?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some non-fiction (or less fictionalized) movies across various genres that are highly regarded and worth watching:\n\n1. **Documentaries**:\n   - **\"The Act of Killing\"** (2012): A powerful documentary about the Indonesian mass killings of 1965-66.\n   - **\"13th\"** (2016): Explores the intersection of race, justice, and mass incarceration in the United States.\n   - **\"Won't You Be My Neighbor?\"** (2018): A heartfelt look into the life and legacy of Fred Rogers.\n   - **\"Citizenfour\"** (2014): Chronicles Edward Snowden's revelations about NSA surveillance.\n   - **\"Blackfish\"** (2013): Examines the consequences of keeping orcas in captivity.\n\n2. **Biographical Movies**:\n   - **\"Schindler's List\"** (1993): The true story of Oskar Schindler, who saved over 1,000 Jews during the Holocaust.\n   - **\"The Social Network\"** (2010): A dramatized account of the creation of Facebook and its impact.\n   - **\"Selma\"** (2014): Depicts the 1965 Selma to Montgomery voting rights marches led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.\n   - **\"A Beautiful Mind\"** (2001): The life of John Nash, a brilliant mathematician who struggled with schizophrenia.\n   - **\"The Theory of Everything\"** (2014): The story of Stephen Hawking\u2019s life and his battle with ALS.\n\n3. **Historical Films**:\n   - **\"Apollo 13\"** (1995): The harrowing true story of the Apollo 13 mission and its astronauts.\n   - **\"Gandhi\"** (1982): Chronicles the life and achievements of Mahatma Gandhi.\n   - **\"12 Years a Slave\"** (2013): The true story of Solomon Northup, a free man who was kidnapped and sold into slavery.\n   - **\"Spotlight\"** (2015): The Boston Globe's investigation into child abuse in the Catholic Church.\n   - **\"The Big Short\"** (2015): Explains the 2008 financial crisis through the eyes of several key players.\n\n4. **Sports Films**:\n   - **\"Raging Bull\"** (1980): The life of boxer Jake LaMotta.\n   - **\"Moneyball\"** (2011): The story of the Oakland Athletics' 2002 season and their unconventional methods.\n   - **\"The Blind Side\"** (2009): The story of NFL player Michael Oher and his journey from homelessness to professional football.\n   - **\"Remember the Titans\"** (2000): Based on the true story of a high school football team overcoming racial tensions.\n   - **\"Rush\"** (2013): The rivalry between Formula 1 drivers James Hunt and Niki Lauda.\n\nThese films offer insightful and often deeply moving portrayals of real-life events and people, making them essential viewing for anyone interested in true stories and historical narratives.",
